# Mail module

Replaces OSSMail/OSSMailScanner/OSSMailView. Messages live in `u_yf_mail_*`; `vtiger_tab` Mail row is `isentitytype=0` (utility module, not CRMEntity).

## Where users configure email

| Who | UI | URL |
|-----|-----|-----|
| User (personal IMAP+SMTP) | **Moje ustawienia** → **Skrzynka pocztowa** | `index.php?module=Users&view=PreferenceMailbox&record=<userId>` |
| Admin (all mailboxes — personal + group) | Settings → **Narzędzia pocztowe** → **Konta pocztowe** | `index.php?parent=Settings&module=MailAccount&view=List` |
| Admin (system SMTP for templates/workflows) | Settings → **Konfiguracja - SMTP** | `index.php?parent=Settings&module=MailSmtp&view=List` |
| Admin (outbound queue, manual send) | Settings → **E-maile do wysłania** | `index.php?parent=Settings&module=Mail&view=ListView` — detail **Manual sending** → `SendManuallyAjax` |

Personal mailbox saves via Ajax (`Mail/SavePersonalAccount`, `TestConnection`) — not the main Users Save button. Requires active encryption (`Settings → Hasła - szyfrowanie`).

**Admin hub (Settings → Konta pocztowe):** unified list (`Account::listAllForAdmin()`). Row click → `Settings/MailAccount/Edit`. Connection UI shared with user self-service: `Mail/MailboxFields.tpl` + `Mail/MailboxForm.js` (PreferenceMailbox + Settings Edit). **Test:** `Mail/TestConnection` only (never save on test). **Personal** edit from Settings: `kind=personal`, save via `Mail/SavePersonalAccount`. **Group** edit: `kind=group`, **Grupa CRM** picker, save via `Settings/MailAccount/SaveAjax`. **Dodaj** creates group account only (`LBL_ADD_GROUP_ACCOUNT`). Users still use PreferenceMailbox for self-service.

**Group accounts:** `kind=group` (ENUM `personal`|`group`; legacy `shared` → `m260708_000001_mail_account_kind_group`), `group_id` → `vtiger_groups`. Save API: **`Account::saveGroup()`** (Settings `MailAccount/SaveAjax`). `Account::syncGroupMembers()` fills `u_yf_mail_account_users` from group membership (`GetGroupUsers`) when the group account is saved **or** when the linked CRM group is saved (`GroupAfterSave` → `Mail_GroupMailboxSync_Handler` → `Account::syncForGroup()`). Manual compose offers this account via `Account::getComposeSenders()` (see `mail-compose.mdc`). List **Typ** column: `LBL_KIND_GROUP` / `LBL_KIND_PERSONAL` (`Settings:MailAccount`).

## Personal account defaults

Org-wide IMAP/SMTP settings (hosts, ports, SSL, inbox/sent folder names) live in **`config/modules/Mail.php`** → `personal_account_defaults`. Per-user mailbox form: **password**, **from_name** (fallback user full name), folders. **Email / IMAP login** = **`vtiger_users.email1`** (read-only in `MailboxFields.tpl` when `MAILBOX_FORM_MODE=personal` or `ACCOUNT_KIND=personal`; no `name`/`username` inputs). Edit email in user profile (`PreferenceDetail` / `PreferenceEdit`), not on the mailbox form. `Account::preparePersonalAccountData()` enforces `username`+`name` from `email1` on save, test, and scan. Never put credentials in config.

**Activation:** `Mail_PersonalMailboxProvision_Handler` auto-creates a shell row (`active=0`, `password_enc` NULL) when user gets `email1`. **Zapisz skrzynkę** posts `SavePersonalAccount` with `activate=1` → IMAP+SMTP test first, then encrypt password and set `active=1`. Until then, yellow banner *LBL_MAILBOX_PENDING_ACTIVATION* is expected. `AUTHENTICATIONFAILED` / `LBL_CONNECTION_FAILED` = mail server rejected credentials (verify in webmail/Thunderbird), not a CRM save bug.

**Pitfall:** provisioned account + empty password field → `Client::testConnection` returns `LBL_CONNECTION_FAILED` (not `LBL_MAIL_PASSWORD_REQUIRED`) because it loads stored password from row id. User must type the mailbox password.

**IMAP folder test (`FolderTree::fromClient`):** use **`getFolders(false)`** (flat `LIST "" "*"`) and build the tree locally in PHP (`buildTreeFromFlat`) — do **not** use webklex `getFolders(true)`. Hierarchical recursive `%` LIST breaks on itconnect.pl when parent folder names contain Polish chars (`Elementy usunięte`): webklex passes UTF-8 in the child pattern, server expects Modified UTF-7 → empty recursive result → `failed to fetch any folders`. `Client::testConnection` runs IMAP login → SMTP → folder list as separate steps: auth failure → `LBL_CONNECTION_FAILED`; SMTP failure → `LBL_MAIL_SMTP_CONNECT_FAILED`; login+SMTP OK but folder LIST/build fails → **`LBL_MAIL_IMAP_FOLDER_LIST_FAILED`** (not generic connection failed).

Merge via `Account::applyPersonalDefaults($data, $userId)` — used on save, test connection, IMAP scan, and `getPersonalForDisplay()` (mailbox form when account missing or fields empty). Group accounts (`kind=group`) skip this.

Cron: `LBL_MAIL_SCAN` → `Mail\Cron\Scanner`; `LBL_MAIL_LOG_PRUNE` → `Mail\Cron\LogPrune`.

## Settings MailAccount pitfalls (2026-06)

- Menu field `LBL_MAIL_ACCOUNTS` must sit under block **`LBL_MAIL_TOOLS`** (`vtiger_settings_field.blockid`). Wrong block label (`LBL_MAIL`) → invisible menu.
- URL `view=List` → class **`ListView`**; file must be `src/Modules/Settings/MailAccount/Views/ListView.php` (not `List.php`). Load `Settings/MailAccount/resources/List.js` in `ListView::getFooterScripts` — page controller is `Settings_MailAccount_List_Js` (not `ListView_Js`).
- **`Module::$virtualListFields`:** must be `protected array` (same as parent) — wrong visibility/type → blank list fatal.
- **`Settings\MailAccount\Models\Module`:** do not override `getInstance()` with a zero-arg signature — fatals vs parent. Set `$name = 'MailAccount'` only.
- **`Settings\MailAccount\Models\Record`:** use parent `BaseModel` (`valueMap`); never `get(string $key)` / `set(string $key)` — incompatible with `BaseModel::get($key)`.
- **`Edit.tpl`:** `{include file='EditContent.tpl'|@vtemplate_path:$QUALIFIED_MODULE}` — not `modules/Settings/MailAccount/…` (Smarty resolves under `layouts/basic/modules/Settings/MailAccount/`).
- Form id `#MailAccountForm`; `Settings_MailAccount_Edit_Js` must override `getForm()` — default `#EditView` is wrong.
- List uses standard `Settings\Base\Views\ListView` + `ListViewContent.tpl`: row click via `data-recordurl` from `Record::getDetailViewUrl()` (→ Edit). No per-row Edit button.
- `Edit.php` `getFooterScripts`: use `$request->getModule()` (not `getModule(false)`) for JS path `modules.Settings.MailAccount.resources.Edit`. Load **`modules.Settings.Vtiger.resources.Edit` first** (defines `Settings_Vtiger_Edit_Js` — without it `Settings_MailAccount_Edit_Js` never registers), then `Mail/MailboxForm.js` + `ImapFolderPicker.js`.
- Menu label: add `LBL_MAIL_ACCOUNTS` to `languages/*/Settings/Vtiger.json` (settings sidebar uses that module for `|t`).

## Pitfalls (real bugs from 2026-06)

- **`Mail\Models\Module` must extend `Base\Models\Module`.** Same class name holds static compose helpers; without extend, `Module::getAll()` / global search fatals on `->get()`.
- **Group mailbox compose access uses `u_yf_mail_account_users`, not a live group join.** `getGroupMailboxForUser()` reads that table (`kind=group`, `active=1`, `can_send=1`). Sync runs on group-account save and on CRM group save (`GroupAfterSave` → `Mail_GroupMailboxSync_Handler`). If a user is in `vtiger_users2group` but missing from compose senders: check **`active=0`** (Test + Save with activate), else re-save the group or `Account::syncForGroup($groupId)`.
- **Use `\App\Db\Query`, not `\yii\db\Query`.** Cron (and some CLI) bootstraps without `Yii::$app->db`; raw Yii Query → `getDb() on null`. Same for `Settings/MailAccount`.
- **No `App\User\User`.** Use `CurrentUser::getId()` or an already-loaded user model's `getId()`.
- **Smarty mailbox include:** `{include file='PreferenceMailbox.tpl'|@vtemplate_path:'Mail'}` (filename only) — see `smarty-templates.mdc`.
- **`s_#__mail_queue` (admin connection):** `\App\Db\Db::getInstance('admin')` — `\App\Db::getInstance` is invalid and fatals (`SendManuallyAjax`, `MassSend`). Send path: **`Outbound::deliverFromQueueRow()`**.

Design reference: `documentation/cr-Mail-module.md`.

## Outbound send (2026-07)

**One queue, one cron handler.** Enqueue → `s_yf_mail_queue` → `MailerTask` / Settings manual send → **`Outbound::deliverFromQueueRow()`** only. No `sendByRowQueue`, no separate legacy branch.

```
enqueue: Outbound::enqueue (CRM) or Mailer::addMail (workflow, notifications, …)
         → params JSON: { sender_ref, mail_message_id? }
cron:    deliverFromQueueRow → account:* → Mail\Smtp\Sender
                              → smtp:*   → Mailer::deliverQueueRow
```

| Entry | Enqueue | CRM row (`u_yf_mail_messages`) |
|-------|---------|--------------------------------|
| Modal / compose | `Outbound::sendFromTemplate` / `sendRaw` | yes — `prepared` until cron |
| Workflow, cron helpers | `Outbound::sendFromTemplateParams` | yes when template path |
| VTEmailTask, notifications, import | `Mailer::addMail` | no — `sender_ref` only |

- **`Mailer::addMail`** requires explicit `params.sender_ref`; missing → `LBL_MAIL_SENDER_REF_REQUIRED`. Pass `params` as **array** (or decode before insert) — pre-encoded JSON string in `params` gets double-wrapped by `$quoteJsonColumn` and `sender_ref` is lost (cron fell back to wrong SMTP before 2026-07 fix).
- Modal/mass send: UI must post `senderRef`; server throws `LBL_MAIL_SENDER_REF_REQUIRED` if absent.
- **`sendFromTemplateParams($params)`** — workflow/template bag; replaces removed `Mailer::sendFromTemplate`.
- Queue table needs **`params` TEXT** column (`m260701_000001_mail_queue_params_column`).
- Dev/test: `config/modules/Mail.php` → `MAIL_FILTER_SEND_ONLY_TO_DOMAIN` (`itconnect.pl` on dev/test hosts).
- **Attachments (CRM outbound):** after `Attachment::storeFromPaths`, enqueue **`Attachment::pathMapForSend($messageId)`** (`storage/Mail/…`) — not staging paths. Staging (`cache/mail-compose/`) is deleted before cron; queue JSON with staging paths → empty attach at SMTP. Cron fallback: `deliverFromQueueRow` uses `pathMapForSend` when queue resolve is empty.
- LinkAction / compose pitfalls: `link-action.mdc`, `mail-compose.mdc`.

## Record mail list (Candidates → Maile tab)

- **Related list:** `Base\Views\RelatedList::processMailRelatedList` → `Mail\Models\Service::getMessagesForRecord()` → `layouts/basic/modules/Mail/RelatedList.tpl`. Must `return $viewer->view(..., true)` and `RelatedList::process()` must `return` it — see `main-layout-views.mdc` (broken layout on URL refresh if echoed).
- Outbound columns: **`send_status`** (`sent` / `failed` / `prepared`) and **opened at** — `LEFT JOIN` subquery on `u_yf_link_action_log` (`action=open`, `mail_message_id`, `MIN(clicked_at)`). Same data on `Mail/Detail.tpl` and `Mail/widgets.tpl`.
- Inbound rows: status/open columns show `—`. Open requires valid tracking pixel in stored `body_html` + import cron; empty `<img src="">` = broken send (see `link-action.mdc` dynamic pitfall).
- **Detail links** from related list / widget: `Module::getMessageDetailUrl($id, $sourceModule, $sourceRecord)` — pass parent context so breadcrumbs and prev/next work.

## Mail detail view (`Mail&view=Detail`)

- `Mail\Views\Detail` + `layouts/basic/modules/Mail/Detail.tpl` — full page (`extends MainLayout`), header with `BreadCrumbs.tpl` + prev/next (same shell as `DetailViewHeader.tpl`, no `Detail.js` dependency).
- Parent context: `sourceModule` + `sourceRecord` query params, else first `u_yf_mail_record_links` row. Breadcrumb trail: parent module → record label → **E-maile** (`Module::getParentRelatedListUrl`) → subject.
- Prev/next: `Service::getAdjacentMessageIds()` — same `date_sent DESC` order as `getMessagesForRecord`; URLs via `getMessageDetailUrl()` keeping source params.

## Inline images (templates → Gmail)

- Template logos/photos use **data-URI** `<img src="data:…">` in HTML. Browsers and FreeCRM Sent view render them; **Gmail strips raw `data:` URLs**.
- **`Mail\Smtp\Sender` must call `PHPMailer::msgHTML()`** — not `$mailer->Body = …` — so data URIs become `multipart/related` MIME with `cid:` parts. Legacy `App\Email\Mailer::content()` already did this.
- PHPMailer `msgHTML()` embeds only **`image/jpeg|gif|png`** data URIs. WebP is not converted at send time.
- **Sidecars:** company logo and user photo `.base64` files must hold PNG (or jpeg/gif) data URIs. Use `Company::embeddedImageBinaryForDataUri()` when building sidecars; user avatars: `user-profile-photos.mdc` (PNG on disk, sidecar via `writeUserPhotoBase64SidecarForRelativeImage`).
